'''''Poseidon Wars 3-D''''' is a 1989 [[Master System]] video game that was released in North America and Europe.

==Gameplay==
The player has just been recruited to the [[United States Navy]] as a cadet.<ref name="mobygames">[http://www.mobygames.com/game/sega-master-system/poseidon-wars-3-d Overview of ''Poseidon Wars 3-D''] at [[MobyGames]]</ref> Like all cadets that serve in the U.S. Navy, the ultimate career goal is to be promoted to [[admiral]].<ref name="mobygames"/> Players must go on various [[tour of duty|tours of duty]] with a submarine and destroy targets like [[battleship]]s and anything vital to the enemy's war efforts.<ref name="mobygames"/> Upon completing a certain amount of missions, the player moves up in the Navy rankings.<ref name="mobygames"/>

If the player runs out of fuel or gets totally damaged, the mission becomes an immediate failure.<ref name="mobygames"/> In this manner, the fuel acts as a sort of time limit that is realistically indicated in-game.

